   "source": [
    "# EMC^2 demo notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook we show an example of how to run EMC2 using ModelE and HSRL data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Populating the interactive namespace from numpy and matplotlib\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import emc2\n",
    "import act\n",
    "%pylab inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load the model data using the ModelE object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_path = 'allvars.SCM_AWR_linft_BT0_unNa_noaer.nc'\n",
    "my_model = emc2.core.model.ModelE(model_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After that, we load in the KAZR data using the KAZR object."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "KAZR = emc2.core.instruments.KAZR('nsa')\n",
    "KAZR.read_arm_netcdf_file('awrkazrcorgeM1.c0.20160816.000001.nc')"
